imdb.title: Ore-tachi ni Tsubasa wa Nai
imdb.plot: Haneda Takashi has a secret he cannot speak of. To leave his dull school-life, he was supposed to have escaped to another world. However, he is reeled in by certain ties on his heart. One of these is Kobato, his awkward younger si...

episodes.title: For Example, That Kind of Fairytale
episodes.plot: DJ Condor is your guide as the everyday lives of several young city-dwellers come into focus on the streets of Yanagihara, a bustling metropolis where there's no shortage of stories.

episodes.title: The Animal I Like Is the Pegasus
episodes.plot: Chronically under-employed Hayato Narita is hired to help a young girl - the sister of a local gang leader - find her stolen bicycle. Meanwhile, Shusuke Chitose is tasked with reviewing the autobiography of an ex-porn star.

episodes.title: Kobato Is Cute, Huh?
episodes.plot: After arriving for his first shift at Karuo's Alexander, Shusuke learns he'll be trained by Hiyoko. Later, when the YFB rumbles with R-Wing, Hayato finds himself in the middle of the action.

episodes.title: Drac... I May Have Gotten Pregnant...
episodes.plot: Ai and Naru create a few awkward situations while competing for Hayato's attention. Meanwhile, some truly unusual events unfold at Alexander involving Kakeru, Shusuke, and a bizarre - and violent - customer.

episodes.title: O, How Virtuous Is Our Honored Hawk!
episodes.plot: Takashi may have trouble grasping the various conditions that go along with "dating" Asuka, but that's nothing compared to facing ten thousand monsters on the field of battle!

episodes.title: Eek! No, I'll Make Noise!
episodes.plot: Chitose gets an eyeful when a grateful Hiyoko tenderly dresses his wound. Later, Drac warns Otori about a dangerous man in a hat.

episodes.title: Your King's Glorious Return!
episodes.plot: Garuda, the King of Gretagard, seizes control of Hayato Narita's body and reunites with his old friend Phoenix. When the king's lusty desires lead him to Kobato, familial relations get super creepy!

episodes.title: No Big-Busted Cream Girl Yet?!
episodes.plot: When Lord Hawk is pierced by a poisoned blade, Sparrow uses her body as a tool to help him expel the venom. Back at school, Takashi gets caught in a tug-of-war between a bossy blonde and a Watarai.

episodes.title: My Heart Is Heaving!!
episodes.plot: Shusuke assumes control of Takashi for the day, Hiyoko hears some heartbreaking criticism of her latest literary effort, and Naru recruits some friends to help find her missing bicycle.

episodes.title: Please, Always Be a Fan, Okay?
episodes.plot: Hayato quickly handles the all-important grad essay situation, and Shusuke manages to save Hiyoko's writing career.

episodes.title: Are You Familiar with the Concept of Little Sister Moe?
episodes.plot: Haneda's day out features a slightly creepy conversation on the forbidden secrets of little sister moe, and Watarai gets physical when her boyfriend disappears into his dreamland!

episodes.title: We With(Out) Wings...
episodes.plot: As Haneda slowly lets go of his fantasy world, he discovers the reason for his very existence and reaches out to those who helped him along the way.
